1) Virtualization:
   Virtualization refers to creating a virtual version of something such as Hardware, OS, storage device, network resources
  
	Infographic data (history of virtualization):
	https://blog.storagecraft.com/infographic-history-virtualization/

	https://docs.oracle.com/cd/E26996_01/E18549/html/VMUSG1010.html

2) What is Docker:
	Docker is software container platform designed to run and deploy applications using containers
	Docker operates in deployment phase and makes the process of deployment easy in multiple environments

3) Docker Architechture:
	Developer ---> Docker File ---> Docker Image ---> Docker Containers
						     ---> DockerHub
	Client(CLI) ---> Server(with containers)

4) Docker Engine:
	Requests from Client to Server as commands/REST 
	All the components of Docker Client and Docker Server forms Docker Engine
	Clients and Server can be present on different hosts			


